  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of emergency shelter assistance to poor and near poor households affected by Typhoon Damrey in Central Viet Nam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide emergency shelter through provision of cash and vouchers for shelter materials in the five provinces most affected by Typhoon Damrey. UNDP will use CERF funds to provide cash/vouchers to 5,000 households as well as to provide short training courses to 27,000 local affected community members on safe house repair and construction. 20,000 beneficiaries will benefit directly from this project, which will be implemented within six months.</narrative>
  </description>
